title: The 10 most important things in the world right now

title: Manchester bomber Salman Abedi 'was a pal of ISIS recruiter'

author: Andreas Nolde
description: Ein günstiges Angebot bei Aldi Nord: Mit dem WLAN-ac-Repeater, den es ab Donnerstag, 24. Mai, gibt, verstärken Sie Ihre WLAN-Netzabdeckung zuhause – für 17,99 Euro.
title: WLAN-Signal zum Hammerpreis verstärken - Aldi macht das möglich

author: By Thomas Burrows, Scott Campbell, Dave Burke, Joseph Curtis and Rachael Burford For Mailonline
description: Troops are to be deployed onto Britain's streets amid fears a further terror attack 'may be imminent'. The PM announced the move less than 24 hours after the bomb attack at a teen concert.
title: BREAKING NEWS: PM says terror threat level is 'critical'

author: Julia Maehner
description: Aldi Süd surft auf der perfekten Wellenlänge: Ab 24. Mai bietet der Discounter in seinen Filialen das Terris Internetradio an. Um es voll auszunutzen, benötigt man aber den Musik-Dienst Aldi Life.
title: Aldi verkloppt Internetradio: Schickes DAB+ Radio beim Discounter

author: talkSPORT
description: You can listen to live commentary of Ajax v Manchester United in the Europa League final on Wednesday, May 24 from 7pm, live on talkSPORT. Clarence Seedorf, a Champions League winner with Ajax, joined the Alan Brazil Sports Breakfast ahead of the big game to share his thoughts.
title: Europa League final: Clarence Seedorf says Ajax are a talented, unpredictable team - but 'maestro' Mourinho will have Manchester United prepared for them

author: Wiebke Hellmann
description: Aldi Nord packt ab Donnerstag, den 24. Mai 2017, das LTE-Smartphone Lenovo B für 69,99 Euro ohne Vertrag in seine Verkaufsregale. Auf Wunsch können Sie das Aldi-Talk Starter-Set im Wert von 10 Euro freischalten. Neben LTE hat das Handy aber noch ein besonderes Feature in dieser Preisklasse.
title: Bei Aldis neuem Smartphone-Deal müsst ihr eure Ansprüche zurückschrauben

author: Greg Wilford
description: More than 714,000 young people have registered to vote since Theresa May called for a snap election, following a series of social media campaigns urging Facebook, Twitter and Snapchat users to sign up.  Under 25s have sent off nearly 16,000 more applications than any other age group since the Prime Minister made the shock announcement on 18 April.    They made up more than a third of the 150,000 potential voters who registered that day - a spike of around 140,000 in 24 hours.
title: More than 700,000 young people have registered to vote in the last month
